[[uid=830lwgrs]] I am afraid that the news I have to
[[uid=830lwgrt]] give you will not altogether please
[[uid=830lwgrw]] you. You are the son of my poor sister,
[[uid=830lwgrx]] Mrs. Moncrieff, and consequently
[[uid=830lwgry]] Algernon’s elder brother.
[[uid=830lwgrz]] 
[[uid=830lwgs0]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgs1]] Algy’s elder brother! Then I have a [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwgs2]] brother after all. I knew I had a
[[uid=830lwgs3]] brother! I always said I had a brother!
[[uid=830lwgs4]] Cecily,—how could you have ever doubted
[[uid=830lwgs5]] that I had a brother? [Seizes hold of
[[uid=830lwgs6]] Algernon.] Dr. Chasuble, my unfortunate
[[uid=830lwgs7]] brother. Miss Prism, my unfortunate
[[uid=830lwgs8]] brother. Gwendolen, my unfortunate
[[uid=830lwgs9]] brother. Algy, you young scoundrel, you
[[uid=830lwgsb]] will have to treat me with more respect
[[uid=830lwgsc]] in the future. You have never behaved
[[uid=830lwgsd]] to me like a brother in all your life.
[[uid=830lwgsf]] 
[[uid=830lwgsg]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwgsh]] Well, not till to-day, old boy, I
[[uid=830lwgsj]] admit. I did my best, however, though I
[[uid=830lwgsk]] was out of practice.
[[uid=830lwgsl]]  [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwgsm]] [Shakes hands.]
[[uid=830lwgsn]] 
[[uid=830lwgsp]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwgsq]] [To Jack.] My own! But what own are
[[uid=830lwgsr]] you? What is your Christian name, now
[[uid=830lwgss]] that you have become some one else?
[[uid=830lwgst]] 
[[uid=830lwgsw]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgsx]] Good heavens! . . . I had quite
[[uid=830lwgsy]] forgotten that point. Your decision on
[[uid=830lwgsz]] the subject of my name is irrevocable,
[[uid=830lwgt0]] I suppose?
[[uid=830lwgt1]] 
[[uid=830lwgt2]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwgt3]] I never change, except in my
[[uid=830lwgt4]] affections.
[[uid=830lwgt5]] 
[[uid=830lwgt6]] CECILY.
[[uid=830lwgt7]] What a noble nature you have,
[[uid=830lwgt8]] Gwendolen!
[[uid=830lwgt9]] 
[[uid=830lwgtb]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgtc]] Then the question had better be cleared
[[uid=830lwgtd]] up at once. Aunt Augusta, a moment. At
[[uid=830lwgtf]] the time when Miss Prism left me in the
[[uid=830lwgtg]] hand-bag, had I been christened
[[uid=830lwgth]] already?
[[uid=830lwgtj]] 
[[uid=830lwgtk]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwgtl]] Every luxury that money could buy,
[[uid=830lwgtm]] including christening, had been
[[uid=830lwgtn]] lavished on you by your fond and doting [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwgtp]] parents.
[[uid=830lwgtq]] 
[[uid=830lwgtr]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgts]] Then I was christened! That is settled.
[[uid=830lwgtt]] Now, what name was I given? Let me know
[[uid=830lwgtw]] the worst.
[[uid=830lwgtx]] 
[[uid=830lwgty]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwgtz]] Being the eldest son you were naturally
[[uid=830lwgw0]] christened after your father.
[[uid=830lwgw1]] 
[[uid=830lwgw2]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgw3]] [Irritably.] Yes, but what was my
[[uid=830lwgw4]] father’s Christian name? [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwgw5]] 
[[uid=830lwgw6]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwgw7]] [Meditatively.] I cannot at the present
[[uid=830lwgw8]] moment recall what the General’s
[[uid=830lwgw9]] Christian name was. But I have no doubt
[[uid=830lwgwb]] he had one. He was eccentric, I admit.
[[uid=830lwgwc]] But only in later years. And that was
[[uid=830lwgwd]] the result of the Indian climate, and
[[uid=830lwgwf]] marriage, and indigestion, and other
[[uid=830lwgwg]] things of that kind.
[[uid=830lwgwh]] 
[[uid=830lwgwj]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgwk]] Algy! Can’t you recollect what our
[[uid=830lwgwl]] father’s Christian name was?
[[uid=830lwgwm]] 
[[uid=830lwgwn]] ALGERNON. [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwgwp]] My dear boy, we were never even on
[[uid=830lwgwq]] speaking terms. He died before I was a
[[uid=830lwgwr]] year old.
[[uid=830lwgws]] 
[[uid=830lwgwt]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgww]] His name would appear in the Army Lists
[[uid=830lwgwx]] of the period, I suppose, Aunt Augusta?
[[uid=830lwgwy]] 
[[uid=830lwgwz]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwgx0]] The General was essentially a man of
[[uid=830lwgx1]] peace, except in his domestic life. But
[[uid=830lwgx2]] I have no doubt his name would appear
[[uid=830lwgx3]] in any military directory.
[[uid=830lwgx4]] 
[[uid=830lwgx5]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgx6]] The Army Lists of the last forty years
[[uid=830lwgx7]] are here. These delightful records
[[uid=830lwgx8]] should have been my constant study.
[[uid=830lwgx9]] [Rushes to bookcase and tears the books
[[uid=830lwgxb]] out.] M. Generals . . . Mallam,
[[uid=830lwgxc]] Maxbohm, Magley, what ghastly names
[[uid=830lwgxd]] they have—Markby, Migsby, Mobbs,
[[uid=830lwgxf]] Moncrieff! Lieutenant 1840, Captain,
[[uid=830lwgxg]] Lieutenant-Colonel, Colonel, General
[[uid=830lwgxh]] 1869, Christian names, Ernest John.
[[uid=830lwgxj]] [Puts book very quietly down and speaks
[[uid=830lwgxk]] quite calmly.] I always told you,
[[uid=830lwgxl]] Gwendolen, my name was Ernest, didn’t
[[uid=830lwgxm]] I? Well, it is Ernest after all. I mean
[[uid=830lwgxn]] it naturally is Ernest.
[[uid=830lwgxp]] 
[[uid=830lwgxq]] LADY BRACKNELL. [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwgxr]] Yes, I remember now that the General
[[uid=830lwgxs]] was called Ernest, I knew I had some
[[uid=830lwgxt]] particular reason for disliking the
[[uid=830lwgxw]] name.
[[uid=830lwgxx]] 
[[uid=830lwgxy]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwgxz]] Ernest! My own Ernest! I felt from the
[[uid=830lwgy0]] first that you could have no other
[[uid=830lwgy1]] name!
[[uid=830lwgy2]] 
[[uid=830lwgy3]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgy4]] Gwendolen, it is a terrible thing for a
[[uid=830lwgy5]] man to find out suddenly that all his
[[uid=830lwgy6]] life he has been speaking nothing but
[[uid=830lwgy7]] the truth. Can you forgive me?
[[uid=830lwgy8]] 
[[uid=830lwgy9]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwgyb]] I can. For I feel that you are sure to [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwgyc]] change.
[[uid=830lwgyd]] 
[[uid=830lwgyf]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgyg]] My own one!
[[uid=830lwgyh]] 
[[uid=830lwgyj]] CHASUBLE.
[[uid=830lwgyk]] [To Miss Prism.] Lætitia! [Embraces
[[uid=830lwgyl]] her]
[[uid=830lwgym]] 
[[uid=830lwgyn]] MISS PRISM.
[[uid=830lwgyp]] [Enthusiastically.] Frederick! At last!
[[uid=830lwgyq]] 
[[uid=830lwgyr]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwgys]] Cecily! [Embraces her.] At last!
[[uid=830lwgyt]] 
[[uid=830lwgyw]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgyx]] Gwendolen! [Embraces her.] At last!
[[uid=830lwgyy]] 
[[uid=830lwgyz]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwgz0]] My nephew, you seem to be displaying
[[uid=830lwgz1]] signs of triviality.
[[uid=830lwgz2]] 
[[uid=830lwgz3]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwgz4]] On the contrary, Aunt Augusta, I’ve now
[[uid=830lwgz5]] realised for the first time in my life
[[uid=830lwgz6]] the vital Importance of Being Earnest.
[[uid=830lwgz7]] 
[[uid=830lwgz8]] TABLEAU